631 Jun
Londen mr. Edmund Warner
mij last to you wash on the 27 cur. to which pleases to be refered, advisingh then that I had
drawne ono you £100 st. for yo acctt. att 35.3 att 1½ 170 payable to the onder of m Leonad
vermeulen for which have recd £176„5:- flaims & past to yd creditt, mogh mich recomanding
you the honour of my bill. now I am without any from you so have yeasterday sent oo
nicuwpoort to m. Michiel vallego one packett q 2 little, ones according to the inclosed envoyce
amonting to ƒ453„14 ¼ in £75„ 12„4½ flemish beeng N. 11 & 12 for which please to give
mee creditt, as also for N13 & 14 am. to £167„130- flemish, which are also ready, butt to
devert risid, if any be, I thought good to send with eves y nessanger, se meting
wee haveing 3 messargers a week for nieurpoort, so att the latter end of nept week
all will be ready where you receave all these goods, you will casely iudge which manner
of ordering or foulding is bott, to comply the better with yd pleasure for the future never
will laces be cheaper then these are, & I doubt, I shall advijss you of rising in less then
whilst this day most of the resting is brought in so that yd order will be compleated, before
the latter end of neyt week, of you finde any p not worth itts price, lett my onely know
the nimber, & I'll know the maker to gett amends whilst now
a 31 d
Londen mr. Henry Colluss
I have before mee yd of 9 & 16 cur. the first I should have answered sooner had
not delayd itt to send yd. acctt. with est, butt m. Maynard & scawen beengh hove hate
hindered itt butt now they are gon, so pnext they follow as for our frind m. warner, ie
is less censibles of is loss thes my teses yett I have not dofisted in perseinting the robbery
butt recovered some part in hopes to recover more, whilst I recomand this to yd seeres
for seeng he doth approve of my doing I shall contnew my endeavour, to which he doth
the more engage mee, by giving ince noless imployment e I am in away for
buying of laces both for spainen & England, & have severall good con., & any that
made try all with mee, didhithers procud, though they have been served by others
for I am of opiniur that noother can out do mee in all respects, if Jean serve you
as for what you wgite censerning cap a brihall, I all tuguire the needfull

Brussel Mons. Jeseren Sabberton
Antwart 2 feb: 1682
in answer to yd of 20: past I am god s be thanchis here well
arrived & hope you shall send mee the desired lace before the latter end
of this weel: I observe that wee aggree in all parcells of our aitto
the ballancs: of which is alvrayers ready citt yo commans, though yon
had occasion for itt in london att 2 usoer elee here att sight: I do send
son this day 4 oper messayen 5 p. oflaces in a packettdineed to you
of which the 2 eraew t pices. are cutl, as also one of 4 huns
ous in sever all necus, desiring yon to gett each madito ghether with
in servor all pcepst desirins & op so iett each made to ghet. hern nith all
sreed imasinable the 2p. for eust ane oully dusty so could mech they
might besclaned &nchtened a litt le so make stom vindable, itt is of
the goods lost about gand, on ths I do depend that they schall
bondy besore the latter end of this week, because I would send
spencovered goode 10 englancs as ter matter of s. proposed
ditseles Ill say as phowckd hart in frest you my aiyd
to send mee all the payketts of lace which ar intended this way, iffor
receaveing & sendeng ferwards of whuch you promuse to pay mest well
uy ves pprovision of each packett or penketts, this all the bene fitt I finde
you propore mee pp recompense wheredt promiss you up vn necvord
of anhonest & sincire mon to be fonth lullto yd pitrest, that nevw
nuy of yd packetts shall bee seen by any marchatt of what placce
soever, pott att the receaving o them shall be sent forward according
ly to yd order & opport nute, & also promis that heveromy other
direitely, or indirettely shall wer know the nomes of them you dee
withall, or the wayes you make nso off in sending terwards of yd
goods, provided they be otheruise then het hertof have made uen vilf
which ane by newport & holland p post, I further promise to recom=
mend all franto dealeurth you, & to have what laces shall
have occasion for rom you allowing 3½ pr to provision & the vallu
ready for capital & provision, this is as much as eom jay, for
whilst I pronie you sencsn & mij endeaveur for yd advantage
as much as for my ownes I shuck itt is as much as can be
exspected fer & sapot aen will have mach more prom meer
then whatt I espert from you, sole accetke rest tht go discete
